01:28:07,454 --> 01:28:10,958
No.
Not like this.

763
01:28:11,458 --> 01:28:13,961
For weeks you've been asking for this.

764
01:28:14,461 --> 01:28:16,964
Well, now you have it.

765
01:28:25,472 --> 01:28:26,974
- What are you doing?
- Nothing.

766
01:28:27,474 --> 01:28:28,934
I'm just taking his teeth.

767
01:28:31,436 --> 01:28:33,939
But you just can't kill a man
for his teeth.

768
01:28:34,439 --> 01:28:35,941
Why not? He has good teeth.

769
01:28:38,443 --> 01:28:39,945
Because--
Because you can't!

770
01:28:42,447 --> 01:28:43,949
What about all this?

771
01:28:44,449 --> 01:28:45,951
But that's different.

772
01:28:47,452 --> 01:28:49,955
I mean, we were fighting for a cause.

773
01:28:50,455 --> 01:28:53,959
Not me.
He's my prisoner...

774
01:28:54,459 --> 01:28:54,960
I can take his teeth
if I want to.

775
01:28:55,460 --> 01:28:58,964
No, you can't!
Stop it!

776
01:28:59,464 --> 01:29:00,966
Here. Take this!

777
01:29:02,467 --> 01:29:04,970
He's mine now.
Here, you.

778
01:29:05,470 --> 01:29:06,972
Go.

779
01:29:09,433 --> 01:29:11,935
Bravo. And what about
all the other prisoners?

780
01:29:12,436 --> 01:29:14,938
- Do we let them go too?
- I don't know.

781
01:29:17,441 --> 01:29:17,941
Maybe.

782
01:29:26,450 --> 01:29:29,953
We must confess.
We must confess.

783
01:29:32,456 --> 01:29:34,958
Please, we have to be confessed.
All of us.

784
01:29:40,464 --> 01:29:42,966
I know this is not normal custom...

785
01:29:43,467 --> 01:29:44,968
but, uh--

786
01:29:49,473 --> 01:29:51,934
Everything's gonna be fine.
He's gonna confess us.

787
01:29:55,437 --> 01:29:57,940
Kneel. Kneel.

788
01:30:09,451 --> 01:30:10,953
Alençon brings bad news.

789
01:30:11,453 --> 01:30:14,957
Thousands of English are forming up
on the far side of the river.

790
01:30:15,457 --> 01:30:17,960
I think we should count our men
and get ready.

791
01:30:19,461 --> 01:30:19,962
Let's go.

792
01:31:00,460 --> 01:31:00,961
I'll go.

793
01:31:04,464 --> 01:31:06,967
Alone.

794
01:31:35,454 --> 01:31:37,956
I have a message for your King Henry!

795
01:31:39,458 --> 01:31:41,960
It is a message from God!

796
01:31:42,461 --> 01:31:43,962
Go home!

797
01:31:47,466 --> 01:31:49,968
Go now, in peace!

798
01:31:51,470 --> 01:31:53,972
If you do not go now,
you will be buried in this field!

799
01:31:57,434 --> 01:32:01,939
I've seen enough blood!

800
01:32:04,441 --> 01:32:05,943
But if you want more...

801
01:32:07,444 --> 01:32:08,946
I can't stop you!

802
01:32:10,447 --> 01:32:13,951
I can only warn you
that it will be your blood...

803
01:32:16,453 --> 01:32:16,954
not ours!

804
01:32:19,456 --> 01:32:21,959
I'm waiting for your answer.

805
01:32:38,433 --> 01:32:40,936
Never wait for miracles.
Stand by to attack.

806
01:32:54,449 --> 01:32:55,951
Please.

807
01:33:03,458 --> 01:33:04,960
My Lord...

808
01:33:06,461 --> 01:33:06,962
please.

809
01:33:39,453 --> 01:33:41,955
Now that's what I call
a goddamn bloody miracle.

810
01:33:42,456 --> 01:33:43,957
She was on her white horse alone...

811
01:33:44,458 --> 01:33:46,960
facing the whole English army,
and she drove them away...

812
01:33:47,461 --> 01:33:49,963
and now Orléans is free.

813
01:34:00,474 --> 01:34:01,934
We lost Orléans.

814
01:34:03,435 --> 01:34:04,937
I want that girl.

815
01:34:08,440 --> 01:34:11,944
I want that girl burned.

816
01:34:32,464 --> 01:34:34,967
May I see the seamstress?
It's too tight. I can't breathe.

817
01:34:35,467 --> 01:34:38,971
That's meant to be a crown?
Don't you have something more regal?

818
01:34:39,471 --> 01:34:40,973
The English took the real one.

819
01:34:41,473 --> 01:34:43,934
It's been muddy so long I forgot
how good it looked cleaned up.

820
01:34:44,434 --> 01:34:46,937
But did you remember to clean up
what's inside as well?

821
01:34:47,437 --> 01:34:50,941
I ask for a grandiose coronation,
and this is what you give?

822
01:34:51,441 --> 01:34:52,943
This whole thing is going to be
an utter fiasco!

823
01:34:54,444 --> 01:34:56,947
You gave me 3 days to prepare.
Your father's coronation took 3 months.

824
01:34:57,447 --> 01:34:58,949
He's right.
We should call for a delay.

825
01:34:59,449 --> 01:35:00,951
No time.
We can't hold up the ceremony.

826
01:35:01,451 --> 01:35:02,953
No telling when the English
might come back.

827
01:35:03,453 --> 01:35:05,956
Let them come. Let them see
who is the true king of France.

828
01:35:16,466 --> 01:35:19,970
Those damn English. We should be
doing this in Paris in Notre Dame.

829
01:35:20,470 --> 01:35:21,972
It is much more prestigious
and twice as big.

830
01:35:22,472 --> 01:35:24,933
It is the sacred place that matters,
not the size. Correct, Bishop?

831
01:35:25,434 --> 01:35:28,937
Yes, my lady.
True kings of France must be anointed...

832
01:35:29,438 --> 01:35:31,940
in our great cathedral of Reims
with the holy oil of Clovis.

833
01:35:43,452 --> 01:35:45,954
Your Grace!
There can be no anointing.

834
01:35:46,455 --> 01:35:49,958
- What are you talking about?
- The holy oil of Clovis is all gone.

835
01:35:50,459 --> 01:35:51,960
Gone?
That's impossible.

836
01:35:52,461 --> 01:35:55,964
It's a magic oil. A miraculous oil.
It can never be exhausted.

837
01:35:56,465 --> 01:35:57,966
- Look for yourself.
- Problem?

838
01:35:58,467 --> 01:35:59,968
I just don't understand.

839
01:36:00,469 --> 01:36:02,971
The oil of Clovis. It was quite full
the last time I saw it.

840
01:36:03,472 --> 01:36:06,934
- And when was that?
- At the coronation of King Charles VI.

841
01:36:07,434 --> 01:36:09,937
Thirty years ago?
Does it surprise you it's gone?

842
01:36:10,437 --> 01:36:12,940
But you don't understand.

843
01:36:13,440 --> 01:36:16,944
It's no ordinary oil.
It's a miraculous oil.

844
01:36:17,444 --> 01:36:20,948
It was brought
by a white dove from heaven...

845
01:36:21,448 --> 01:36:22,950
to crown King Clovis
in this very cathedral.

846
01:36:25,452 --> 01:36:27,955
- What are you doing?
- Performing a miracle.

847
01:37:48,452 --> 01:37:51,955
With this sacred oil, blessed by
the hand of God the Father Almighty...

848
01:37:52,456 --> 01:37:54,958
we do anoint thee, Charles Valois...

849
01:37:55,459 --> 01:37:59,963
to be sovereign lord and king
of this great kingdom of France...

850
01:38:00,464 --> 01:38:03,967
charging that we should defend
the faith of our Mother Holy Church...

851
01:38:05,469 --> 01:38:06,970
as long as we shall live.

852
01:38:08,472 --> 01:38:09,973
Amen.

853
01:38:44,466 --> 01:38:45,968
Long live the king!

854
01:39:04,444 --> 01:39:07,948
- Jeanne, are you all right?
- Yes, I'm fine.

855
01:39:10,450 --> 01:39:13,954
- Why are you staring at me?
- You have an arrow in your leg.

856
01:39:20,460 --> 01:39:20,961
So there is.

857
01:39:23,463 --> 01:39:24,965
But that doesn't stop you
from climbing!

858
01:39:26,466 --> 01:39:29,970
Well, climb! Go! Go!

859
01:39:35,434 --> 01:39:36,935
Take this arrow out of my leg.

860
01:39:42,441 --> 01:39:43,942
Look out!

861
01:39:45,444 --> 01:39:48,947
- Be careful!
- Jeanne, the men are exhausted.

862
01:39:49,448 --> 01:39:51,950
I know, but so is the enemy.
They're falling back. Paris is ours.

863
01:39:52,451 --> 01:39:53,952
Jeanne, we are not enough.

864
01:39:54,453 --> 01:39:56,955
So bring up the reinforcements.

865
01:39:57,456 --> 01:39:58,957
Reinforcements? Where?

866
01:40:00,459 --> 01:40:01,960
Right behind us.

867
01:40:02,461 --> 01:40:04,963
Dunois with another 10,000 men.

868
01:40:05,464 --> 01:40:07,966
- Jeanne, look behind you.
- Never look behind. Only ahead.

869
01:40:10,469 --> 01:40:12,971
Do you know how to count?

870
01:40:15,432 --> 01:40:18,936
Of course I do!
So, bring them up!

871
01:40:22,439 --> 01:40:25,943
Jeanne, that is not
10,000 reinforcements!

872
01:40:26,443 --> 01:40:27,903
That is 100...

873
01:40:28,403 --> 01:40:30,948
very loyal
but very tired soldiers!

874
01:40:33,450 --> 01:40:34,952
But where's Dunois?

875
01:40:35,452 --> 01:40:36,954
And where are the men
the king promised me?

876
01:40:37,454 --> 01:40:40,916
He never sent them!
Don't you understand?

877
01:40:41,458 --> 01:40:42,960
He doesn't want this war anymore.

878
01:40:43,460 --> 01:40:45,963
He has his crown now.
That's all he ever wanted.

879
01:40:47,464 --> 01:40:50,968
But my voices, they promised me.

880
01:40:51,468 --> 01:40:52,928
To hell with your voices!

881
01:40:56,473 --> 01:40:58,934
It's time to face facts!

882
01:41:01,436 --> 01:41:03,897
We have nothing to do here!

883
01:41:04,398 --> 01:41:05,941
None of us!

884
01:41:08,443 --> 01:41:09,945
Not even you.

885
01:41:15,450 --> 01:41:17,953
You don't believe in me anymore?

886
01:41:18,453 --> 01:41:20,956
Jeanne, of course we still
believe in you.

887
01:41:21,456 --> 01:41:24,960
If it were up to me, I'd chase every
goddamn Englishman into the ocean.

888
01:41:25,460 --> 01:41:27,963
But it's not up to us anymore.

889
01:41:28,422 --> 01:41:29,923
It's up to the king.

890
01:41:42,436 --> 01:41:43,937
You should go home, Jeanne.

891
01:41:59,453 --> 01:42:01,955
We cannot possibly afford to pay
for the size of army she's demanding.

892
01:42:03,457 --> 01:42:03,957
Girl is crazy.

893
01:42:06,418 --> 01:42:07,961
Her victory at Orléans
was a miracle.

894
01:42:08,462 --> 01:42:11,965
But we can't wait for a miracle
when we build a future for France.

895
01:42:14,468 --> 01:42:16,970
Paris was a disaster.

896
01:42:17,429 --> 01:42:18,931
God wasn't with her then.

897
01:42:19,473 --> 01:42:21,934
If God deserts her,
what do you think we should do?

898
01:42:34,446 --> 01:42:37,950
Why did you betray me? Paris was ours.
All I needed was a few hundred men.

899
01:42:38,450 --> 01:42:42,913
- Why did you take the army you gave me?
- Gave you?

900
01:42:43,455 --> 01:42:45,958
- I wouldn't quite put it that way.
- So how would you put it?

901
01:42:51,463 --> 01:42:54,925
We are, of course,
enormously grateful...

902
01:42:55,425 --> 01:42:56,969
for your past efforts...

903
01:42:57,469 --> 01:42:59,972
but now your task is done.

904
01:43:00,472 --> 01:43:01,974
Now is the time for negotiation.

905
01:43:02,474 --> 01:43:04,935
Peace will only be got with the English
by the end of a lance.

906
01:43:05,394 --> 01:43:08,939
Why are you so blood thirsty?
Do you enjoy it?

907
01:43:12,442 --> 01:43:13,944
Diplomacy is far more civilized...

908
01:43:14,444 --> 01:43:16,947
far safer and far cheaper.

909
01:43:25,455 --> 01:43:29,960
I've letters here from towns under
siege, where your people are starving...

910
01:43:30,419 --> 01:43:32,963
begging God on their knees
to help them.

911
01:43:33,463 --> 01:43:36,967
I'm here to answer their prayers.
And you want to stop me?

912
01:43:39,469 --> 01:43:41,972
France does not belong to you, Charles.

913
01:43:42,472 --> 01:43:44,933
She belongs to God.

914
01:43:56,445 --> 01:43:57,946
If only she would just go home.

915
01:44:18,467 --> 01:44:19,927
So what am I supposed to do now?

916
01:44:21,470 --> 01:44:23,972
- What do your voices say?
- They haven't spoken to me in weeks.

917
01:44:24,473 --> 01:44:26,934
Not since the coronation.

918
01:44:27,434 --> 01:44:28,936
No signs, nothing.

919
01:44:30,437 --> 01:44:31,897
Maybe their silence is a sign.

920
01:44:34,441 --> 01:44:35,943
- Maybe it's a sign to go home.
- No.

921
01:44:36,443 --> 01:44:38,946
It's not time yet.
My mission isn't over yet.

922
01:44:41,448 --> 01:44:44,910
- There's still more I have to do.
- But how do--

923
01:44:45,452 --> 01:44:46,954
How do you know that these--

924
01:44:47,454 --> 01:44:49,957
these voices aren't just really you?

925
01:44:51,458 --> 01:44:55,921
Well, they are me.
That's how God speaks to me.

926
01:44:57,422 --> 01:45:00,968
Even you could hear them
if you listened hard enough.

927
01:45:03,470 --> 01:45:04,972
You make it sound so simple.

928
01:45:06,473 --> 01:45:08,892
So even you don't believe in me anymore.

929
01:45:09,434 --> 01:45:13,939
Jeanne, I believe in you
more than anyone.

930
01:45:14,439 --> 01:45:16,942
I just wish I could...

931
01:45:17,442 --> 01:45:18,944
help you.

932
01:45:20,404 --> 01:45:21,947
There is one thing you can do
if you want to help me.

933
01:45:23,448 --> 01:45:23,949
Tell me.

934
01:45:24,449 --> 01:45:25,951
Tell the king to give back
the army that he gave me.

935
01:45:37,462 --> 01:45:38,964
We have to stop her, Your Majesty.

936
01:45:39,464 --> 01:45:42,968
If she raises an army
and attacks the Burgundians...

937
01:45:43,468 --> 01:45:45,929
months of negotiations
will have been in vain.

938
01:45:47,472 --> 01:45:48,974
Jeanne has done so much for us.

939
01:45:49,433 --> 01:45:52,936
I can assure you, the maid has
no greater admirer than myself.

940
01:45:53,437 --> 01:45:55,939
Whatever our personal feelings,
we cannot allow her to conduct...

941
01:45:56,398 --> 01:45:58,942
her own private war.

942
01:45:59,443 --> 01:46:02,946
For the sake of the kingdom, you must
stop her from going to Compiègne.

943
01:46:03,447 --> 01:46:04,948
I can't stop her.

944
01:46:05,449 --> 01:46:10,954
Well, if you don't, I'm sure the
Burgundians would be happy to oblige.

945
01:46:11,455 --> 01:46:12,956
If they capture her at Compiègne--

946
01:46:13,457 --> 01:46:14,958
No one could blame us.

947
01:46:17,461 --> 01:46:21,924
But it could sound like
we betrayed her.

948
01:46:22,424 --> 01:46:24,968
- No, never.
- Good heavens, no.

949
01:46:25,469 --> 01:46:26,970
Don't worry, Charles.

950
01:46:29,473 --> 01:46:33,894
If God is still with her,
she will be victorious.

951
01:46:34,394 --> 01:46:35,938
But her army's so much smaller.

952
01:46:36,438 --> 01:46:38,941
Then her faith will have to be bigger.

953
01:46:53,455 --> 01:46:56,959
- What are you doing? Open this gate.
- I can't risk the safety of my town.

954
01:47:00,462 --> 01:47:00,963
Take my banner!

955
01:47:59,396 --> 01:48:00,939
My Lord.

956
01:48:02,441 --> 01:48:03,942
My Lord.

957
01:48:29,468 --> 01:48:30,969
I can't believe it.

958
01:48:31,470 --> 01:48:35,933
Your romantic vision of death
with all that grass growing everywhere.

959
01:48:36,391 --> 01:48:37,935
I must admit,
you have a big imagination.

960
01:48:38,435 --> 01:48:40,938
But maybe not big enough.

961
01:48:41,438 --> 01:48:44,942
Death is much more simple.

962
01:48:49,446 --> 01:48:51,949
After a few months,
it gets more interesting.

963
01:48:55,452 --> 01:48:58,956
Then after a year,
it finally becomes...

964
01:49:01,416 --> 01:49:02,960
romantic.

965
01:49:08,465 --> 01:49:08,966
Who are you?

966
01:49:09,466 --> 01:49:11,969
You don't like my face?

967
01:49:12,427 --> 01:49:14,972
Maybe you'd prefer this one.

968
01:49:18,433 --> 01:49:19,935
Too young, maybe.

969
01:49:20,435 --> 01:49:22,938
How about this one?

970
01:49:24,398 --> 01:49:28,944
Better now? But incomplete.

971
01:49:35,450 --> 01:49:37,911
Get thee behind me, Satan.

972
01:49:38,453 --> 01:49:42,958
Who are you to even think you can know
the difference between good and evil?

973
01:49:45,460 --> 01:49:45,961
Are you God?

974
01:49:50,424 --> 01:49:52,968
I'm just a messenger.

975
01:49:53,468 --> 01:49:54,970
He needs me.

976
01:49:55,470 --> 01:49:58,974
How can you imagine that God,
the creator of heaven and Earth...

977
01:49:59,433 --> 01:50:00,934
the source of all life...

978
01:50:01,435 --> 01:50:04,938
could possibly need you?

979
01:50:06,440 --> 01:50:06,940
I don't know.

980
01:50:08,442 --> 01:50:09,943
You don't think He's big enough
to deliver His own messages?

981
01:50:11,445 --> 01:50:13,947
What do you want from me?

982
01:50:14,448 --> 01:50:15,949
Nothing.
I'm here to set you free.

983
01:50:19,453 --> 01:50:20,954
I said smile.
You have visitors.

984
01:50:21,455 --> 01:50:22,956
The Duke of Burgundy.

985
01:50:35,469 --> 01:50:37,971
So here's the famous Jeanne...

986
01:50:38,472 --> 01:50:40,974
savior of Orléans,
terror of the English.

987
01:50:41,433 --> 01:50:44,937
My king will pay
any ransom you ask.

988
01:50:45,437 --> 01:50:48,941
Your king?
Oh, yes, of course.

989
01:50:49,441 --> 01:50:50,943
What's he gonna pay me with?
Cows? Chickens?

990
01:50:52,444 --> 01:50:54,947
I prefer gold,
and the English have plenty.

991
01:50:56,448 --> 01:50:59,952
I wonder how much they'll pay to have
the witch of Orléans in their clutches.

992
01:51:00,452 --> 01:51:04,957
The English are so arrogant, they can't
accept being defeated by a peasant girl.

993
01:51:05,457 --> 01:51:07,960
It has to have been the devil's work.

994
01:51:08,460 --> 01:51:09,962
God defeated the English.

995
01:51:10,462 --> 01:51:12,965
And God allowed you to be caught?

996
01:51:14,466 --> 01:51:15,968
Personally, I don't believe in God.

997
01:51:16,468 --> 01:51:18,971
I don't believe in the devil either.

998
01:51:19,471 --> 01:51:21,974
That's why I'm never disappointed.

999
01:51:24,434 --> 01:51:24,935
Sell her.

1000
01:51:42,452 --> 01:51:43,954
To pay Jeanne's ransom.

1001
01:51:44,454 --> 01:51:46,957
The captains gave what they could,
as well as citizens of Orléans.

1002
01:51:47,457 --> 01:51:51,962
That's very generous of you.
How much?

1003
01:51:52,462 --> 01:51:54,965
- Ten thousand gold crowns.
- Ten thousand?

1004
01:51:55,465 --> 01:51:56,967
That's a lot.

1005
01:51:57,467 --> 01:52:00,971
Your Grace, I place you in charge
of this very delicate negotiation.

1006
01:52:16,445 --> 01:52:18,947
Get yourself ready.
You're leaving.

1007
01:52:22,451 --> 01:52:22,951
Who are you?

1008
01:52:23,452 --> 01:52:26,955
Pierre Cauchon, bishop of Beauvais.

1009
01:52:27,456 --> 01:52:29,958
As you were captured in my diocese, the
duty to conduct the trial falls upon me.

1010
01:52:32,461 --> 01:52:34,963
Trial?
What trial?

1011
01:52:35,464 --> 01:52:38,967
Your trial, Jeanne,
on a charge of heresy.

1012
01:52:42,471 --> 01:52:43,972
But my king--

1013
01:52:46,433 --> 01:52:47,935
Didn't he pay my ransom?

1014
01:52:48,435 --> 01:52:50,938
It seems the English care
more about you than the French.

1015
01:52:51,438 --> 01:52:52,940
- The English?
- Yes.

1016
01:52:53,440 --> 01:52:54,942
They paid your ransom.

1017
01:52:55,442 --> 01:52:58,946
Tomorrow you'll be transferred
to their great castle at Rouen.

1018
01:54:01,466 --> 01:54:04,970
Our serene and Christian king, Henry VI,
king of England and France...

1019
01:54:05,470 --> 01:54:07,973
has placed this girl in our hands,
accused of heretical deeds...

1020
01:54:08,473 --> 01:54:09,933
to be tried in a matter of faith.

1021
01:54:10,434 --> 01:54:12,936
Take the Holy Gospels in your hand...

1022
01:54:13,437 --> 01:54:16,940
and swear to tell the truth regarding
anything you may be asked.

1023
01:54:18,442 --> 01:54:21,945
I don't know what you will ask me. You
may ask things I won't want to answer.

1024
01:54:22,446 --> 01:54:24,948
You will swear to tell the truth
about everything you are asked.

1025
01:54:26,450 --> 01:54:29,953
I will willingly tell the truth
about all Earthly things.

1026
01:54:30,454 --> 01:54:33,957
But as to my revelations,
I've told no one except my king...

1027
01:54:35,459 --> 01:54:37,961
Charles VII, the one and only
king of France.

1028
01:54:41,465 --> 01:54:42,966
You must take the oath.

1029
01:54:43,467 --> 01:54:46,970
Not even a king would refuse to take
an oath in a matter of faith.

1030
01:54:47,471 --> 01:54:48,972
I will tell you all
that I'm allowed to tell you.

1031
01:54:51,433 --> 01:54:52,935
But as for the rest...

1032
01:54:53,435 --> 01:54:55,938
even if you threatened
to cut off my head, I won't tell you.

1033
01:55:02,444 --> 01:55:05,948
Begin by telling us your name, assuming
you're allowed to tell us that much.

1034
01:55:08,450 --> 01:55:08,951
My name is Jeanne.

1035
01:55:11,453 --> 01:55:13,956
My little cross was taken from me.
May I have it back?

1036
01:55:14,456 --> 01:55:17,960
Show us a little more
cooperation first.

1037
01:55:18,460 --> 01:55:19,962
Where were you born?

1038
01:55:20,462 --> 01:55:22,965
In a village called Domremy.

1039
01:55:23,465 --> 01:55:24,967
How old are you?

1040
01:55:25,467 --> 01:55:26,969
Nineteen, or thereabouts.

1041
01:55:27,469 --> 01:55:28,971
Were you baptized?

1042
01:55:30,472 --> 01:55:32,933
- Yes.
- Recite our Lord's Prayer.

1043
01:55:35,435 --> 01:55:37,938
Not unless you hear my confession.

1044
01:55:42,442 --> 01:55:43,944
Listen to me very carefully.

1045
01:55:44,444 --> 01:55:46,947
We are all men of faith...

1046
01:55:47,447 --> 01:55:50,951
and we shall earnestly strive for the
salvation of your body and your soul...

1047
01:55:51,451 --> 01:55:55,956
in the name of our Church who never
closes arms to those who return to her.

1048
01:55:56,456 --> 01:55:57,958
But we cannot help you...

1049
01:55:58,458 --> 01:56:00,961
unless you submit to our
learned judgment and authority.

1050
01:56:01,461 --> 01:56:03,964
Take heed of this
charitable admonition...

1051
01:56:04,464 --> 01:56:06,967
for if you persist
in refusing our help...

1052
01:56:07,467 --> 01:56:10,971
we shall have no choice but to
abandon you to the secular powers.

1053
01:56:11,471 --> 01:56:13,974
And I think you know well enough
the punishment that would await you.

1054
01:56:20,439 --> 01:56:21,940
Now...

1055
01:56:22,441 --> 01:56:24,943
will you please recite
our Lord's Prayer?

1056
01:56:27,446 --> 01:56:29,948
Not unless you hear my confession.

1057
01:56:33,452 --> 01:56:37,956
Be careful. You aren't helping yourself
by refusing to submit to our judgment.

1058
01:56:38,457 --> 01:56:39,958
You...

1059
01:56:40,459 --> 01:56:42,961
who claim to be my judges,
you be careful!

1060
01:56:44,463 --> 01:56:46,965
For you too one day will be judged.

1061
01:56:47,466 --> 01:56:47,966
Guards, take the prisoner away!

1062
01:56:51,470 --> 01:56:53,972
- Silence!
- Sorceress!

1063
01:56:54,473 --> 01:56:56,934
Silence!
Clear the room!

1064
01:56:57,434 --> 01:56:59,937
Clear the room!

1065
01:57:02,439 --> 01:57:05,943
In future, we should conduct inquiries
privately, away from public pressure.

1066
01:57:06,443 --> 01:57:08,946
Let the English burn her if they want.
Why does it have to involve us?

1067
01:57:10,447 --> 01:57:12,950
Because it's our duty to root out
heresy wherever we find it.

1068
01:57:15,452 --> 01:57:15,953
Father Vincente.

1069
01:57:18,455 --> 01:57:19,957
You're the most venerable among us.
What do you think?

1070
01:57:21,458 --> 01:57:22,960
I think this trial is a masquerade...

1071
01:57:23,460 --> 01:57:25,963
and I won't be part of it anymore.

1072
01:57:26,463 --> 01:57:28,966
I'm willing to be her judge,
but not her executioner.

1073
01:57:29,466 --> 01:57:30,968
That's what I'm trying to ensure.

1074
01:57:34,471 --> 01:57:39,935
The verdict comes at the end of
a trial, Cauchon. Not at the beginning.

1075
01:57:42,437 --> 01:57:43,939
I am going back to Rome...

1076
01:57:44,439 --> 01:57:46,942
to give my report
to our Holy Father, the Pope.

1077
01:57:50,445 --> 01:57:53,949
This is ridiculous. Now I'm the one
who's on trial and being judged.

1078
01:57:54,449 --> 01:57:55,951
- Arrest him.
- What are you doing?

1079
01:57:57,452 --> 01:57:59,955
This is an ecclesiastical court.
You've no right to do this.

1080
01:58:00,455 --> 01:58:01,957
This is English territory.

1081
01:58:02,457 --> 01:58:03,959
I have the right to do anything.

1082
01:58:04,459 --> 01:58:05,961
Is that clear?

1083
01:58:23,437 --> 01:58:23,937
Our Father who art in heaven--

1084
01:58:24,438 --> 01:58:25,939
Thy kingdom come--

1085
01:58:31,445 --> 01:58:32,946
Forgive us--
Forgive them--

1086
01:58:33,447 --> 01:58:36,950
Forgive them, then forgive us.
Forgive them.

1087
01:58:37,451 --> 01:58:37,951
Why were you yelling?

1088
01:58:43,457 --> 01:58:46,960
What are you doing here?
You can't stay here! Go away!

1089
01:58:47,461 --> 01:58:49,963
Why? Are you waiting for someone else?

1090
01:58:51,465 --> 01:58:51,965
Yes.

1091
01:58:53,467 --> 01:58:54,968
- Who?
- My visions.

1092
01:58:55,469 --> 01:58:56,970
Your visions.

1093
01:58:58,472 --> 01:58:59,973
They're going to visit you in here?

1094
01:59:00,474 --> 01:59:02,935
Yes. That's what I pray for.

1095
01:59:04,436 --> 01:59:06,939
I want to see that.
Do you mind if I stay on the side here?

1096
01:59:07,439 --> 01:59:08,941
- I won't bother you.
- No!

1097
01:59:10,442 --> 01:59:11,944
No, you can't! You can't!

1098
01:59:12,444 --> 01:59:13,946
- Or else they won't come.
- Why won't they?

1099
01:59:14,446 --> 01:59:15,948
Because I have to be alone.

1100
01:59:16,448 --> 01:59:19,952
Oh. They won't come anyway.

1101
01:59:21,453 --> 01:59:23,956
- What do you mean, they won't come?
- Why would they?

1102
01:59:25,457 --> 01:59:27,960
Because I've always been faithful
to God...

1103
01:59:28,460 --> 01:59:29,962
and I've followed everything
He's ever said...

1104
01:59:30,462 --> 01:59:31,964
and I've done everything
He's ever asked me to do.

1105
01:59:32,464 --> 01:59:33,966
God asked you to do something?

1106
01:59:38,470 --> 01:59:39,972
Yes, lots of things.

1107
01:59:40,472 --> 01:59:42,933
You mean, God said...

1108
01:59:43,433 --> 01:59:44,935
''I need you, Jeanne''?

1109
01:59:48,438 --> 01:59:50,941
But He's sent me signs.

1110
01:59:53,443 --> 01:59:54,945
Signs? What signs?

1111
01:59:57,447 --> 01:59:58,949
The wind. The wind.

1112
02:00:04,454 --> 02:00:04,955
Wind.

1113
02:00:05,455 --> 02:00:07,958
And the clouds. Ringing.

1114
02:00:10,460 --> 02:00:11,962
Ringing cloud.

1115
02:00:13,463 --> 02:00:14,965
The dance. The dance.

1116
02:00:29,438 --> 02:00:31,940
The sword. The sword lying in the field.

1117
02:00:33,442 --> 02:00:33,942
That was a sign.

1118
02:00:34,443 --> 02:00:37,946
No. That was a sword in a field.

1119
02:00:39,448 --> 02:00:41,950
No. No. That was a sign.

1120
02:00:42,451 --> 02:00:44,953
No, that was a sword in a field.

1121
02:00:45,454 --> 02:00:48,957
It can't just get there by itself.
It can't.

1122
02:00:49,458 --> 02:00:51,960
A sword just doesn't get there
by itself.

1123
02:00:52,461 --> 02:00:56,965
True. Every event has an infinite
number of causes, so why pick one?

1124
02:00:57,466 --> 02:00:58,967
There are many ways a sword
might find itself in a field.

1125
02:01:05,474 --> 02:01:07,935
Seems a perfectly valid explanation,
but how about this one?

1126
02:01:14,441 --> 02:01:15,943
Then again, there are other
possibilities.

1127
02:01:21,448 --> 02:01:21,949
Or even faster.

1128
02:01:26,453 --> 02:01:28,956
And that's without counting
the inexplicable.

1129
02:01:31,458 --> 02:01:34,962
Yet from an infinite number of
possibilities, you had to pick this one.

1130
02:01:49,434 --> 02:01:52,938
You didn't see what was, Jeanne.

1131
02:01:53,438 --> 02:01:55,941
You saw what you wanted to see.

1132
02:02:13,458 --> 02:02:15,961
This voice that you say
appears to you...

1133
02:02:16,461 --> 02:02:20,966
is it an angel or a saint,
or does it come from God?

1134
02:02:21,466 --> 02:02:24,970
I won't tell you any more about that.

1135
02:02:25,470 --> 02:02:27,973
I'm more afraid of displeasing Him
than not answering you.

1136
02:02:28,473 --> 02:02:32,936
You're afraid of displeasing God
by telling the truth?

1137
02:02:33,437 --> 02:02:35,939
Did God forbid you
to tell the truth?

1138
02:02:36,440 --> 02:02:39,943
My revelations were for
the king of France, not for you.

1139
02:02:42,446 --> 02:02:44,948
When you saw your king
for the first time...

1140
02:02:45,449 --> 02:02:46,950
was there an angel over his head?

1141
02:02:47,451 --> 02:02:48,952
If there was one, I did not see it.

1142
02:02:49,453 --> 02:02:51,955
Why did your king believe in you
without any proof?

1143
02:02:53,457 --> 02:02:54,958
Go ask him yourself.

1144
02:03:08,472 --> 02:03:08,972
Dinner.

1145
02:03:26,448 --> 02:03:28,951
When you were taken prisoner,
did you have a horse?

1146
02:03:29,451 --> 02:03:31,954
Yes. A half-steed. Black.

1147
02:03:33,455 --> 02:03:34,957
- Who gave you that horse?
- My king.

1148
02:03:35,457 --> 02:03:37,960
How many did he give you?

1149
02:03:40,462 --> 02:03:41,964
Five steeds...

1150
02:03:42,464 --> 02:03:44,967
and a few hackneys.

1151
02:03:45,467 --> 02:03:47,970
As much as for a lord.
What an honor.

1152
02:03:48,470 --> 02:03:50,973
Did your king give you other wealth
apart from those horses?

1153
02:03:53,433 --> 02:03:55,936
What about all those dresses
you were given?

1154
02:03:56,436 --> 02:03:57,938
Silk dresses, weren't they?

1155
02:03:59,439 --> 02:03:59,940
Yes.

1156
02:04:00,440 --> 02:04:02,943
Yes, I was given a few.

1157
02:04:03,443 --> 02:04:06,947
But I never had time to wear them.

1158
02:04:07,447 --> 02:04:09,950
Still, pretty wealthy
for a peasant girl, wouldn't you say?

1159
02:04:13,453 --> 02:04:16,957
You look pretty wealthy
for a servant of God, wouldn't you say?

1160
02:04:22,462 --> 02:04:23,964
You launched an attack on Paris,
didn't you?

1161
02:04:24,464 --> 02:04:25,966
I tried to.

1162
02:04:27,467 --> 02:04:28,969
And didn't you order the citizens
of Paris to surrender the city...

1163
02:04:29,469 --> 02:04:29,970
in the name of the King of Heaven?

1164
02:04:30,470 --> 02:04:33,974
No. I said, ''Surrender in the name
of the king of France.''

1165
02:04:34,433 --> 02:04:36,935
That is not what is written
in the evidence.

1166
02:04:39,438 --> 02:04:39,938
Look yourself.

1167
02:04:40,439 --> 02:04:42,941
I can't read.

1168
02:04:45,444 --> 02:04:47,946
Yes, I forgot.

1169
02:04:48,447 --> 02:04:51,950
God sent us an illiterate peasant
to carry out such an important mission.

1170
02:04:52,451 --> 02:04:53,952
Do you think that God
made the right decision?

1171
02:04:54,453 --> 02:04:57,956
To take an ignorant girl
to save the kingdom of France?

1172
02:04:58,832 --> 02:04:59,333
I leave that answer to God.

1173
02:05:04,838 --> 02:05:06,340
Fuck!

1174
02:05:06,840 --> 02:05:08,342
Calm down, my lord.
I beg you.

1175
02:05:08,842 --> 02:05:11,345
How can I when I'm made
the laughing stock of the whole court?

1176
02:05:11,845 --> 02:05:13,347
You've seen how it is.
This girl has a way with people...

1177
02:05:13,847 --> 02:05:16,308
but we're making progress every day.

1178
02:05:16,808 --> 02:05:20,312
As long as that bitch remains alive,
our armies refuse to fight. Understand?

1179
02:05:20,812 --> 02:05:21,313
They need proof
that God is on their side.

1180
02:05:22,814 --> 02:05:24,316
It's not for us to burn her.
That's your prerogative.

1181
02:05:24,816 --> 02:05:26,318
And it's your prerogative
to find her guilty!

1182
02:05:26,818 --> 02:05:30,322
But we can't do that
unless she admits to blasphemy.

1183
02:05:30,822 --> 02:05:31,323
What are you waiting for?

1184
02:05:31,823 --> 02:05:35,327
You've got a castle full of racks,
ropes and pulleys. Torture the bitch!

1185
02:05:35,827 --> 02:05:38,330
You'll never get anything
out of her that way.

1186
02:05:38,830 --> 02:05:40,332
And besides...

1187
02:05:40,832 --> 02:05:46,338
you must realize that several
of my colleagues are, well, scared.

1188
02:05:46,839 --> 02:05:48,340
Scared? Of a girl?

1189
02:05:48,841 --> 02:05:51,343
Scared to make a mistake.

1190
02:05:51,844 --> 02:05:53,345
Suppose she's right.

1191
02:05:53,846 --> 02:05:56,348
Suppose she has been sent by God.

1192
02:06:00,811 --> 02:06:05,315
- Who's side are you on, Cauchon?
- I'm on the side of Holy Mother Church.

1193
02:06:06,817 --> 02:06:08,318
Do you have a sword?

1194
02:06:10,821 --> 02:06:12,322
- Quite a few.
- Didn't you also carry a banner?

1195
02:06:13,824 --> 02:06:15,325
Yes.

1196
02:06:15,826 --> 02:06:18,328
Which do you prefer?
Your banner or your sword?

1197
02:06:18,829 --> 02:06:20,330
I was 40 times more fond of my banner.

1198
02:06:20,831 --> 02:06:23,333
Why? Did it have some
particular value or power?

1199
02:06:26,837 --> 02:06:28,338
It's just--

1200
02:06:28,839 --> 02:06:31,341
- A sword is a weapon.
- And?

1201
02:06:32,843 --> 02:06:37,347
And so, I prefer my banner.

1202
02:06:37,848 --> 02:06:38,348
Why?

1203
02:06:38,807 --> 02:06:41,310
To avoid killing anyone.

1204
02:06:41,810 --> 02:06:44,313
Are you saying if you'd not
been carrying your banner...

1205
02:06:44,813 --> 02:06:46,315
you'd have killed more people?

1206
02:06:50,819 --> 02:06:52,321
Of course not.
I never killed anyone.

1207
02:06:52,821 --> 02:06:55,324
Then perhaps the temptation...

1208
02:06:55,824 --> 02:06:57,326
to kill would have been stronger--

1209
02:06:57,826 --> 02:06:59,328
too strong, perhaps.

1210
02:07:00,829 --> 02:07:02,331
I warned the English to go back home.

1211
02:07:02,831 --> 02:07:05,334
I begged them not to force us to fight.
They knew that I--

1212
02:07:05,834 --> 02:07:08,337
We have numerous witnesses
who can confirm...

1213
02:07:08,837 --> 02:07:10,339
you were not always
carrying your banner.

1214
02:07:14,843 --> 02:07:16,345
Yes, perhaps.

1215
02:07:16,845 --> 02:07:18,347
Sometimes you were carrying
just your sword.

1216
02:07:20,807 --> 02:07:21,308
Yes. I don't know.

1217
02:07:21,808 --> 02:07:24,311
Did you use the sword
you held in your hand?

1218
02:07:24,811 --> 02:07:26,313
Yes, I used it--
I held it up--

1219
02:07:26,813 --> 02:07:29,316
You held up your sword
and flourished it about like this!

1220
02:07:29,816 --> 02:07:30,317
I don't remember.

1221
02:07:30,817 --> 02:07:33,320
So, you were on the battlefield
with your sword in your hand...

1222
02:07:34,821 --> 02:07:37,324
waving it above your head,
charging against the enemy...

1223
02:07:37,824 --> 02:07:39,326
screaming at the enemy,
fighting for your life...

1224
02:07:39,826 --> 02:07:41,328
and you expect us to believe...

1225
02:07:41,828 --> 02:07:45,332
that in the middle
of all this excitement...

1226
02:07:45,832 --> 02:07:49,336
you never killed anyone.

1227
02:07:49,837 --> 02:07:52,339
No. I never killed anyone.

1228
02:07:54,842 --> 02:07:56,343
I can't believe
you can lie like that.

1229
02:07:56,844 --> 02:08:00,347
I'm not lying. I'm not lying.
Leave me alone. I can't remember.

1230
02:08:00,848 --> 02:08:03,308
-I didn't kill anyone. I can't remember.
-Let me help your memory.

1231
02:08:03,809 --> 02:08:06,311
I don't want to hear any more.
Leave me alone. I didn't kill that man.

1232
02:08:06,812 --> 02:08:08,313
Leave me alone!

1233
02:08:08,814 --> 02:08:11,316
Stop. Stop. I can't remember.

1234
02:08:11,817 --> 02:08:15,320
The battles were so confusing. I was
only defending myself as best I could.

1235
02:08:15,821 --> 02:08:19,324
There was so much dust, smoke and noise.
I was being attacked on all sides.

1236
02:08:19,825 --> 02:08:22,327
So maybe perhaps I fought back.

1237
02:08:22,828 --> 02:08:25,330
- But it was only to defend myself.
- So your memory's coming back.

1238
02:08:25,831 --> 02:08:27,332
- Yes.
- Good.

1239
02:08:27,833 --> 02:08:31,336
Now, you tell me why God let all those
battles happen in the first place.

1240
02:08:31,837 --> 02:08:33,338
He's so powerful. You said...

1241
02:08:33,839 --> 02:08:35,340
'' He's the creator of heaven and Earth,
the source of all life.''

1242
02:08:35,841 --> 02:08:39,344
He could easily have stopped
all that blood and misery.

1243
02:08:39,845 --> 02:08:40,345
Why didn't He--

1244
02:08:40,846 --> 02:08:43,348
Is He the one who spread
all that blood and misery?

1245
02:08:43,807 --> 02:08:45,309
- Is He?
- No. But He could have stopped it.

1246
02:08:45,809 --> 02:08:48,312
What, did he get pleasure--
pleasure--

1247
02:08:48,812 --> 02:08:52,316
pleasure from watching us killing
each other in His name?

1248
02:08:52,816 --> 02:08:54,318
In His name?

1249
02:08:54,818 --> 02:08:58,322
In His name. We fought and killed
in His name--

1250
02:08:58,822 --> 02:09:00,324
- the King of Heaven.
- Really?

1251
02:09:00,824 --> 02:09:02,326
Let all those who love me
follow me!

1252
02:09:03,827 --> 02:09:05,329
'' Let all who love me
follow me!''

1253
02:09:05,829 --> 02:09:08,332
Where does God get mentioned?

1254
02:09:08,832 --> 02:09:10,334
Come on, Jeanne.

1255
02:09:10,834 --> 02:09:12,336
Be honest.

1256
02:09:12,836 --> 02:09:15,339
You fought for yourself.
In your name.

1257
02:09:15,839 --> 02:09:17,341
No!

1258
02:09:17,841 --> 02:09:20,344
I was defending myself
as best as I could.

1259
02:09:20,844 --> 02:09:22,346
Everyone has the right
to defend themselves, don't they?

1260
02:09:23,847 --> 02:09:25,349
Yes, they do!
Should I have let myself get killed?

1261
02:09:25,807 --> 02:09:27,309
- Is that it?
- No. You did fine.

1262
02:09:27,809 --> 02:09:29,311
I'd even say well done.

1263
02:09:29,811 --> 02:09:31,313
As a matter of fact...

1264
02:09:31,813 --> 02:09:34,316
most of the ones you killed
probably deserved it, don't you think?

1265
02:09:38,820 --> 02:09:41,323
I never thought killing each other
would bring about any peace.

1266
02:09:41,823 --> 02:09:42,324
I agree.

1267
02:09:42,824 --> 02:09:44,326
Peace will only be got from
the English at the end of a lance.

1268
02:09:44,826 --> 02:09:47,329
I don't agree. Why do you keep
changing your mind all the time?

1269
02:09:49,831 --> 02:09:51,333
You. Why--

1270
02:09:51,834 --> 02:09:54,336
Why are you doing this to me?

1271
02:09:54,837 --> 02:09:56,338
Do you get pleasure from hurting me?

1272
02:09:56,839 --> 02:10:00,342
Pleasure.
That's a difficult word to define.

1273
02:10:02,845 --> 02:10:06,348
When does pain end and pleasure begin?
When did your pleasure begin?

1274
02:10:06,849 --> 02:10:10,310
With that sword in your hand?

1275
02:10:12,813 --> 02:10:15,315
I never took pleasure...

1276
02:10:15,816 --> 02:10:17,317
in hurting anyone.

1277
02:10:18,819 --> 02:10:20,320
Really?

1278
02:10:45,846 --> 02:10:49,308
Set me free. Set me free.

1279
02:10:49,808 --> 02:10:50,309
You will be, Jeanne.

1280
02:10:52,811 --> 02:10:54,313
You will be.

1281
02:11:15,834 --> 02:11:17,336
Jeanne, my very dear
friend in Christ...

1282
02:11:17,836 --> 02:11:19,338
we, your judges and assessors...

1283
02:11:19,838 --> 02:11:22,341
desirous of reaching
a true and lawful verdict...

1284
02:11:22,841 --> 02:11:25,344
submitted a transcript of your trial
to the University of Paris...

1285
02:11:25,844 --> 02:11:27,346
to attain their opinion.

1286
02:11:27,846 --> 02:11:29,348
After careful consideration...

1287
02:11:29,848 --> 02:11:31,308
the learned scholars
have concluded with us...

1288
02:11:31,808 --> 02:11:35,312
that you have committed
many grievous sins.

1289
02:11:35,812 --> 02:11:38,315
I ask you now
to listen most carefully...

1290
02:11:38,815 --> 02:11:41,318
to their opinion,
as detailed in these articles.

1291
02:11:44,821 --> 02:11:45,322
Article One.

1292
02:11:45,822 --> 02:11:49,326
You said that by God's command you have
continually worn men's clothes...

1293
02:11:49,826 --> 02:11:52,329
and that you have also worn
your hair short...

1294
02:11:52,829 --> 02:11:55,332
with nothing to distinguish you from
the soldiers with whom you fought.

1295
02:11:59,837 --> 02:12:01,338
Don't abandon me. Please.

1296
02:12:03,841 --> 02:12:07,344
Where are You?

1297
02:12:07,845 --> 02:12:09,346
Where are You? Please.

1298
02:12:13,809 --> 02:12:16,311
Is this what You want?

1299
02:12:17,813 --> 02:12:20,315
You want me to...

1300
02:12:20,816 --> 02:12:23,318
to burn...

1301
02:12:23,819 --> 02:12:25,320
without...

1302
02:12:25,821 --> 02:12:27,322
being confessed?

1303
02:12:27,781 --> 02:12:30,325
Finally, Article 12.

1304
02:12:30,826 --> 02:12:33,328
You have said that you are not
willing to submit yourself...

1305
02:12:33,787 --> 02:12:36,331
to the judgment of the church militant,
but only to God.

1306
02:12:37,833 --> 02:12:38,333
As to this article,
the scholars say...

1307
02:12:39,835 --> 02:12:41,336
that you have no comprehension
of the authority of the Church.

1308
02:12:41,837 --> 02:12:44,298
That you have perniciously erred
in the faith of God...

1309
02:12:44,840 --> 02:12:48,343
and you are a child of superstition,
a wanderer from the faith...

1310
02:12:48,844 --> 02:12:52,347
an invoker of demons, an idolater...

1311
02:12:52,806 --> 02:12:54,308
and a heretic.

1312
02:13:05,819 --> 02:13:08,280
We once again admonish,
beg and exalt you...

1313
02:13:08,822 --> 02:13:12,326
to cast out and recant
your erroneous beliefs...

1314
02:13:12,826 --> 02:13:15,329
by signing this recantation.

1315
02:13:16,788 --> 02:13:17,331
Please.

1316
02:13:19,833 --> 02:13:21,335
If the Church...

1317
02:13:21,835 --> 02:13:24,338
wants me to say...

1318
02:13:24,838 --> 02:13:27,341
that my visions are evil...

1319
02:13:27,841 --> 02:13:30,344
then I do not believe in this Church.

1320
02:13:35,807 --> 02:13:36,308
Perform your office.

1321
02:13:42,773 --> 02:13:44,316
Wait.

1322
02:13:48,820 --> 02:13:51,323
Jeanne, I beg of you, sign.

1323
02:13:51,823 --> 02:13:54,326
In God's name, don't you understand?
I'm trying to save you.

1324
02:13:54,826 --> 02:13:57,287
I want to be confessed.

1325
02:13:58,830 --> 02:14:00,332
Sign this and I will confess you
myself, if you want.

1326
02:14:01,834 --> 02:14:05,337
And may I--

1327
02:14:05,796 --> 02:14:08,340
May I go to Mass?

1328
02:14:08,841 --> 02:14:10,342
As often as you like.

1329
02:14:10,843 --> 02:14:13,345
Now, for the love of God, sign.

1330
02:14:18,809 --> 02:14:22,312
Sign, Jeanne,
and you'll be free of your chains.

1331
02:14:22,813 --> 02:14:24,314
Free of the fire, Jeanne.

1332
02:14:59,766 --> 02:15:01,310
Thank you.

1333
02:15:04,813 --> 02:15:07,316
Do you know what you just signed?

1334
02:15:08,817 --> 02:15:10,277
You just signed away His existence.

1335
02:15:12,821 --> 02:15:16,325
- I didn't mean to.
- For you, He's a lie.

1336
02:15:18,785 --> 02:15:20,329
An illusion.

1337
02:15:20,787 --> 02:15:22,331
No, no.

1338
02:15:22,789 --> 02:15:24,333
He told me that I would be confessed.

1339
02:15:25,834 --> 02:15:28,337
In the end, it was you
who abandoned Him.

1340
02:15:35,802 --> 02:15:38,347
- May I have that back, please?
- You have nothing to regret.

1341
02:15:40,807 --> 02:15:43,310
Give it back to me!

1342
02:15:43,810 --> 02:15:46,271
- Give it back!
- Take her away!

1343
02:15:51,818 --> 02:15:53,320
Silence her!

1344
02:15:57,783 --> 02:16:00,327
There. She has recanted.

1345
02:16:00,827 --> 02:16:02,329
And we accept her repentance...

1346
02:16:02,829 --> 02:16:06,333
for the Church never closes her arms
to those who would return to the fold.

1347
02:16:07,793 --> 02:16:11,296
Now she's your martyr, not ours.

1348
02:16:38,824 --> 02:16:40,325
Please!

1349
02:16:46,790 --> 02:16:48,292
Enough.

1350
02:16:54,840 --> 02:16:57,342
Here.

1351
02:16:57,843 --> 02:17:00,304
If you want to get dressed,
try these for size.

1352
02:17:07,811 --> 02:17:09,313
My lord bishop.

1353
02:17:19,823 --> 02:17:21,325
Come to see for yourself.

1354
02:17:21,825 --> 02:17:23,285
Well, take a look.

1355
02:17:28,832 --> 02:17:31,335
You see?
Dressed as a man again.

1356
02:17:31,835 --> 02:17:33,295
Her touching repentance
didn't last very long, did it?

1357
02:17:35,797 --> 02:17:40,344
The Bishop of Senlis was passing by
and was on hand to witness her relapse.

1358
02:17:42,846 --> 02:17:45,349
And by what miracle did these clothes
find their way in here?

1359
02:17:45,807 --> 02:17:47,267
Not a miracle, my dear Cauchon.

1360
02:17:47,809 --> 02:17:50,312
An evil spell.

1361
02:17:50,771 --> 02:17:53,315
This girl is a witch,
and tomorrow she will burn for it.

1362
02:17:55,817 --> 02:17:58,320
Have the stake prepared
in the market place.

1363
02:18:13,794 --> 02:18:17,339
Jeanne, I don't understand.
Why did you do it?

1364
02:18:17,840 --> 02:18:19,341
- Why?
- And you.

1365
02:18:19,842 --> 02:18:21,343
Why did you lie?

1366
02:18:21,844 --> 02:18:23,345
You promised to have me confessed.

1367
02:18:23,804 --> 02:18:26,306
I know. It was the only way
to have you saved from the fire.

1368
02:18:26,807 --> 02:18:29,309
It's not my body I want to save.

1369
02:18:29,810 --> 02:18:31,311
It's my soul.

1370
02:18:32,813 --> 02:18:35,274
I ask only one thing.

1371
02:18:35,774 --> 02:18:39,319
Please, hear my confession.

1372
02:18:43,824 --> 02:18:46,285
I can't, Jeanne.
I can't hear your confession.

1373
02:18:50,789 --> 02:18:52,291
I'm very sorry.

1374
02:19:13,770 --> 02:19:15,314
You want to confess?

1375
02:19:19,818 --> 02:19:21,320
I'm listening.

1376
02:19:21,820 --> 02:19:24,281
I've committed sins, my Lord.

1377
02:19:27,826 --> 02:19:29,328
So many sins.

1378
02:19:32,831 --> 02:19:36,335
I saw so many signs.

1379
02:19:36,793 --> 02:19:38,337
Many signs.

1380
02:19:40,839 --> 02:19:42,341
The ones I wanted to see.

1381
02:19:48,847 --> 02:19:51,266
I fought...

1382
02:19:54,811 --> 02:19:56,313
out of revenge...

1383
02:19:59,816 --> 02:20:01,276
and despair.

1384
02:20:08,825 --> 02:20:11,328
I was all the things...

1385
02:20:11,787 --> 02:20:15,290
that people believe...

1386
02:20:15,791 --> 02:20:17,334
they're allowed to be...

1387
02:20:17,793 --> 02:20:20,337
when they're fighting for...

1388
02:20:24,842 --> 02:20:25,342
a cause.

1389
02:20:26,802 --> 02:20:28,303
For a cause.

1390
02:20:30,848 --> 02:20:32,307
I was...

1391
02:20:34,810 --> 02:20:36,311
proud...

1392
02:20:37,771 --> 02:20:39,273
and...

1393
02:20:42,818 --> 02:20:43,318
stubborn.

1394
02:20:44,820 --> 02:20:45,320
Selfish.

1395
02:20:46,822 --> 02:20:48,282
Selfish.

1396
02:20:48,824 --> 02:20:51,326
Yes. Cruel.

1397
02:20:54,830 --> 02:20:56,331
Yes.

1398
02:20:56,832 --> 02:20:58,333
Cruel.

1399
02:21:00,794 --> 02:21:02,296
You think you are ready now?

1400
02:21:07,843 --> 02:21:08,343
Yes.

1401
02:21:10,846 --> 02:21:12,347
Good.

